Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/CallForOralEvidence
Object: A call by a committee or committees conducting an inquiry for a named witness to provide oral evidence.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/inCapacity
Object: Relates a contribution to the incumbency of the person making the contribution e.g. a person making a contribution in their capacity of holding a CEO position of an organisation.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/CallForEvidence
Object: An open call by a committee or committees conducting an inquiry for members of the public or organisations to provide written evidence. Sometimes referred to as a call for written submissions.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/
Object: Ontology to describe calls from Parliament for submission of evidence and resulting submissions.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/callDescription
Object: Relates any type of call to its descriptive text.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/Compelled
Object: A call by a committee or committees conducting an inquiry compelling a named witness to provide oral evidence.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/compelledToAttend
Object: Relates a compelled call for oral evidence to a calendar event where the witness is expected to be heard.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/callEnds
Object: The date time at which a call ends.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/Contribution
Object: A contribution by an individual or organisation to a committee inquiry. This might be in the form of written evidence, oral evidence, papers or records.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/callForPapers
Object: Relates a call for papers to a contribution made in response to that call.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/callForRecords
Object: Relates a call for records to a contribution made in response to that call.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/CallForPapers
Object: A call by a committee or committees conducting an inquiry for a named individual or organisation to provide papers. Papers are understood to be documents that the individual or organisation are unlikely to possess but would be able to compile.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/Call
Object: A call by a committee or committees conducting an inquiry for written evidence, oral evidence, papers or records.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/callForOralEvidence
Object: Relates a call for oral evidence to a contribution made in response to that call.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/focusOfContribution
Object: Relates a contribution to its focus (subject) area(s).

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/Incumbency
Object: A position held by a person for a period of time e.g. Philip Hammond occupying the position of Foreign Secretary between two dates.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/respondsToCall
Object: Relates any type of contribution to the call it is submitted in response to.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/contributes
Object: Relates a contribution to a document contributed.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/Event
Object: An event. A thing that happens over a time interval.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/Focus
Object: A focus area for a contribution. Borrowed from the formal body ontology to identify the subject area or areas covered by a contribution.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/CallForRecords
Object: A call by a committee or committees conducting an inquiry for a named individual or organisation to provide records. Records are understood to be documents that the individual or organisation are known to possess.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/makesContribution
Object: Relates a person making a contribution to their contribution.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/calledAt
Object: The date time at which a call is made.

Subject: http://parliament.uk/ontologies/submission/CalendarEvent
Object: A planned or arranged event in a place.
